sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant W as Browser<br/>(web-app)
    participant API as Identity Core API
    participant BIO as Biometric Service<br/>(internal-only)
    participant PGB as PostgreSQL<br/>biometric_db (pgvector)
    participant PGI as PostgreSQL<br/>identity_core

    note over BIO: continued from part (a):<br/>frame passed liveness + anti-spoof

    BIO->>BIO: face detection -- MTCNN
    alt no face or multiple faces
        BIO-->>API: 400 face detection error
        API-->>W: retry capture
    else single face
        BIO->>BIO: quality score Q = 0.4 blur +<br/>0.3 lighting + 0.3 size,<br/>pose penalty x0.7
        alt Q below enrollment floor 40
            BIO-->>API: 400 poor image quality {Q}
            API-->>W: retry with better lighting/pose
        else Q at or above 40
            BIO->>BIO: Facenet512 embedding<br/>(DeepFace, 512-dim, L2-normalised)
            BIO->>PGB: UPSERT face_embeddings --<br/>vector(512) + Fernet ciphertext<br/>(store-of-record) + key_version<br/>ON CONFLICT (user_id, tenant_id)
            note right of PGB: ANN index on the live DB:<br/>HNSW, cosine ops<br/>(m=16, ef_construction=64)
            BIO-->>API: 200 {quality_score,<br/>liveness_score, dimension: 512}
            API->>PGI: one transaction:<br/>user_enrollments FACE = ENROLLED<br/>+ quality/liveness scores,<br/>users.is_biometric_enrolled = true
            API->>PGI: audit log (enrollment event)
            API-->>W: 200 enrolled {scores}
            note over W: user can now select FACE<br/>as a login factor
        end
    end
